item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: mears
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: About
item.dc:creator: mears
item.content:encoded:
Global Exteriors has been serving Saskatoon since 1994. Over the years, owners and brothers Brian and Andy Fehr have grown the business from a few small teams to managing more than a dozen crews. With more than 20 years spent working in Saskatoon, we have long relationships with some of the top home builders in the city. Our specialty is residential exteriors: new and renovated, multi-family and single home. We are experts in siding and soffit, windows and doors, and eavestroughs and insulation. But if you need exterior work done outside our expertise -- like stonework, roofing, or building an addition -- we have access to companies we trust who can finish the job. Andy and Brian started in the housing industry working with their dad, and they stayed in the family line of work. Brian worked in siding installation for 15 years before starting Global Exteriors with Andy. Their time on the ground has given them a product knowledge that's hard to beat. Global Exteriors only provides the best products on the market. We ensure quality workmanship through careful oversight. A foreman visits our sites daily, and every site is inspected by either Andy or Brian upon completion. We also have a full time service person available to answer any questions once the work is done.

COMMUNITY OUTREACH

Global Exteriors is a community-minded company; we want to improve the quality of both the homes we work on, and the neighbourhoods where our clients live. To that end, we support Youth for Christ Saskatoon, the local chapter of a worldwide Christian movement. Andy has sat on the YFC Sask board of directors for more than a decade, helping to organize tons of fun experiences and activities for kids, including our newest initiative, the Mobile Youth Centre.

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value:
WANT TO JOIN THE TEAM?

We are looking for both employees and subcontractors with appropriate experience who want to work in a fast-paced, well-organized work environment. If youre interested in joining our team, please drop off a resume at our office at 833 Cynthia Street, or send a resume to Brian at brian@globalexteriors.com.

item.title: Services & Products
item.dc:creator: mears
item.content:encoded:
Whether were doing the installation ourselves or helping you DIY, Global Exteriors only offers the best products. We have access to a wide variety of suppliers, tapping Canadas top brands to outfit your homes exterior.

SERVICES

VINYL SIDING
The popular choice among todays consumers, vinyl siding requires little maintenance and is ideal for Saskatchewans tough climate.
SOFFIT, FASCIA, AND TRIM
A vital element to any homes appearance, our top-quality soffit, fascia, and trim products add that perfect finishing touch.
WINDOWS AND DOORS
Enhance the look of your home while improving energy efficiency. We can provide any style you want for your home.
EAVESTROUGHS
All of our eavestroughs are expertly crafted in-house in a wide range of colours and sizes to suit all of your needs.

PRODUCTS

item.title: DIY Tips
item.dc:creator: mears
item.content:encoded: [caption id="attachment_835" align="alignright" width="500"] Our showroom at 833 Cynthia Street has samples of our available products. Stop by to see what we have, and to chat with our knowledgeable staff.[/caption] Are you ready to DIY? Installing siding yourself can save you money, but before you embark on a project check your skill level: Do you feel confident? Have you done projects like this before? Are you a naturally handy or crafty person? If so, great! The next step is preparation. Vinyl siding is the best choice for do-it-yourself projects because it's easier to remove, alter, and reinstall than any other type of siding, and the only special tool you'll need for the job is an unlocking tool, or zip tool. We have some great sources to help guide you through the process: Gentek Vinyl Products Installation Guide Kaycan Vinyl Siding Estimating and Installation Guide Mitten How to Install Guide Once you have a plan in place, you'll need to choose the right materials. That's where the experts at Global Exteriors come in. We have a full range of DIY-friendly products, which you can see in our showroom, and we're happy to give advice and answer any questions you have. Siding is like putting together a big puzzle, and it's even easier with the right guidance from experts who have tackled the challenge before. So what are you waiting for? Get a siding estimate, or give us a ring if you have any questions.
